<font color="#FF0000">OH MY GOD - TENNIS SHOES??</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 30 20:08:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Quick note to Ed Ramon - You can make fun of my thoughts, not like my clothing, put me down and say that I need &quot;midol&quot; (a drug for menstral cramps) and continue on name calling, that I am a wharf rat, a &quot;dock&quot; any other silly names, but, BUT, HOW DARE YOU BAD MOUTH MY SHOES?<br><br>
Being I am a former long-haired-pinko-maggot-ridden-commie-sign-carrying-protestor-who-got-more men killed with ideas than with bullets, you overlooked the most obvious of all.How dare you insult me by saying I wear Tennis shoes. Are you trying to shame me in front of the entire international brotherhood of protestors?  Will I have to turn in my little red book because of this?  <br><br>
Tennis shoes. Oh the shame. That implies that I also wear socks. OH GOD, SOCKS. What embarassment. I wear Sandles man, I wear sandles. Leather Sandles, what else (just like Jesus).  What self respecting leftie would wear Tennis Shoes?  I might as well have on Wingtips with a spit shine over the spam stains. Oy the shame if this gets out. You finally got me where it really hurts, you got me in the soul (you should pardon the pun eddieboy).<br><br>
Seriously Edward, I think you are reaching a new low with your name calling, and I wish, for your sakes, that you'd get it out of your system and act like an adult again. Once was funny, twice was pushing, now you have a choice. Contribute some thinking, some thoughts, some ideas, or continue on with this immature name calling. Think about it.<br><br>
doc spatz
